Subject: [PATCH 117/124] Merged PR 11722846: Config changes before introducing
 kexec

Config changes before introducing kexec

For module validation in VTL1, the module structure must match exactly
between VTL0 and VTL1. In other words, the configs around the different
fields in the module structure must match. Introduce the following
config changes in lvbs.config to match with mshv_sk_config:

	CONFIG_MODULE_SIG_FORCE=y
	CONFIG_IMA=n

Introduce the following config changes for VTL1 kexec support in
mshv_sk_config.

	CONFIG_KEXEC_FILE=y
	CONFIG_KEXEC_SIG=y
	CONFIG_KEXEC_BZIMAGE_VERIFY_SIG=y
	CONFIG_KEXEC_CORE=y

CONFIG_KEXEC_JUMP is enabled for hibernation. In this, the kernel jumps
back to the original kernel from the new kernel. This is something we
cannot support in LVBS in principle. So, disable CONFIG_KEXEC_JUMP, if
CONFIG_HEKI is enabled.

CONFIG_KEXEC is a feature that directly loads the segments from user
space instead of loading a file that contains the segments. Since we
need a signed kexec file to be loaded for LVBS, we will not support
CONFIG_KEXEC.

Signed-off-by: Madhavan T. Venkataraman <madvenka@linux.microsoft.com>

